	COMMON/ISCBUF/IBUF
C
C Buffer into which the digitiser can place its raw data.
C ISIZE comes from /PARAMS/ (n.b. the buffer must be longword aligned,
C and if it is not, the call to SCBUF will round up to the next longword
C boundary, and subtract an appropriate amount from ISIZE)
C
	INTEGER*2 IBUF(ISIZE)
C end of /ISCBUF/
